==Trivia==
*In the comics, Kate Bishop took on the moniker of '''Hawkeye''' after [[Clint Barton]]'s death. When Barton was revived by [[Wanda Maximoff]], they started to work with each other, sharing the "Hawkeye" mantle. She is also a member of the [[w:c:marvel:Young Avengers|Young Avengers]].
**In the ''[[Hawkeye (TV series)|Hawkeye]]'' episodes ''[[Hide and Seek]]'' and ''[[Echoes]]'', the lights in the [[Tracksuit Mafia]]'s [[KB Toys Store]] base flash the date September 5, 2012 in Morse code, the release date of the first appearance of Kate Bishop in [[Matt Fraction (writer)|Matt Fraction's]] 2012 ''Hawkeye'' comic run, ''Hawkeye'' (Vol. 4) #2.<ref>[https://metro.co.uk/2021/12/29/hawkeye-5-things-we-learnt-from-director-rhys-thomas-after-finale-15838281 Hawkeye: From ‘super deep cut’ Kate Bishop Easter Egg to Kevin Feige’s involvement in Rogers The Musical, 5 things we learnt from director Rhys Thomas]</ref>

==Behind the Scenes==
*[[Hailee Steinfeld]] has stated that she has signed a multi-project deal to play Kate Bishop in future installments of the [[Marvel Cinematic Universe]].<ref>[https://collider.com/hailee-steinfeld-interview-dickinson-season-2/ Hailee Steinfeld on the Family of 'Dickinson' Season 2 and the Excitement of 'Hawkeye']</ref>
*Before [[Hailee Steinfeld]] was cast as Kate Bishop, {{WPS|Olivia Cooke}} and {{WPS|Taissa Farmiga}} were in the running for the role.
*[[Hailee Steinfeld]] was encouraged to accept the role of Kate Bishop by [[Finn Jones]], with whom she worked in ''{{WPS|Dickinson (TV series)|Dickinson}}''.<ref>[https://www.digitalspy.com/tv/ustv/a35500932/marvel-finn-jones-hailee-steinfeld-advice/ Marvel's Finn Jones shares casting advice he gave Hawkeye's Hailee Steinfeld]</ref>
*According to [[Carlos Navarro]], the screen test for his character had Kate Bishop's dialogue, but the character was named ''Margarita Black'' instead.<ref>[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=KhDbUsS8hxo Interviewing Carlos Navarro (HAWKEYE) || GEEK ZONE - YouTube] (Translated from Spanish)</ref>
*[[Renae Moneymaker]], [[Caitlin Dechelle]], and [[Holly Dowell]] were stunt doubles for [[Hailee Steinfeld]] in the role of Kate Bishop.
*According to [[Trinh Tran]], Bishop was 8 years old during the [[Battle of New York]].{{Ref|TMoHE}} However, she was previously revealed to be 22 during the events of ''Hawkeye'' ([[2024|Christmas 2024]]) thus making her 9 years old during the events of ''[[The Avengers]]''.
*[[Kathryn Newton]] previously auditioned for the character.

